Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.98,0:00:03.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, did you watch TV yesterday?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.98,0:00:04.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Watch what?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.94,0:00:07.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it obvious? "The News Crew Saw it!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.65,0:00:11.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Startling Truth Behind 'Hassie, '\Nthe Giant Eel of Lake Hamana."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.03,0:00:12.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I watched that, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.57,0:00:15.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way something like that exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.28,0:00:17.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Upon seeing its true nature, the ghost\Nproved to be a beckoning flower,"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.74,0:00:19.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is that what you're saying, Hotaro?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.20,0:00:23.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're such a wet blanket.\NHave you no sense of adventure?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.08,0:00:24.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Am I right, Chi-{\i1}chan{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.21,0:00:27.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am curious as to the truth of\Nwhether it really exists or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.17,0:00:29.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it doesn't matter\Nif it exists or not,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.13,0:00:32.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but today, I hope that it does.\NWouldn't that be more fun?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.97,0:00:36.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All ghosts are just beckoning flowers.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.26,0:00:37.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That sounds like you, Hotaro.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.89,0:00:45.35,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I scowled at the wind blowing\Nat my window of boredom{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.35,0:00:53.36,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}so I could turn away\Nthe awkwardness I was feeling{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.65,0:01:01.58,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Hyouka
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.58,0:01:07.00,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I nod noncommittally at today\Nas I hold it in my hand{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.00,0:01:12.38,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}projecting myself a little exaggeratedly{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.38,0:01:17.89,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I get the feeling that\Nsomething is about to change{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.89,0:01:22.97,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's all because of you\Ncalling out to my heart{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.35,0:01:29.77,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Peeking up at cloudy skies,\NI sense what's coming{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.77,0:01:37.78,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Let's reach out our hands\Nwith courage stronger than ever{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.24,0:01:42.83,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Light and shadow are both still far off{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.83,0:01:49.08,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}but even so, we want to know\Nthe reason for this kindness{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.08,0:01:56.51,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Let's go look now, beyond the brilliance\Nthat goes by nobody's name{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.51,0:02:04.56,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}before it all becomes a thing of the past{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.90,0:02:12.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Classic Lit Club of Kamiyama\NHigh School consists of four members.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.90,0:02:14.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Upon Seeing the True Nature
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.98,0:02:16.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The reason\Nwhy we are being bounced around on this bus
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.57,0:02:17.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, can I have some of those, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.03,0:02:20.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,has to do, of course, with where this bus is going.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.32,0:02:22.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Its last stop is at Zaizen Village,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.12,0:02:23.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,famous for its mountain\Nclimbing and hot springs.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.95,0:02:26.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We are headed there, not for the mountains,\Nbut for the hot springs.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.87,0:02:30.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a fitting activity for one who lives by the principle\Nthat during summer vacation, one should vacate.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.58,0:02:31.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.92,0:02:35.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you so much for what you\Ndid regarding my uncle, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.80,0:02:39.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And, since it's the break, let's all\Ngo to the hot springs together.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.59,0:02:41.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go to the hot springs!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.26,0:02:41.39,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to go
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.39,0:02:44.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.26,0:02:47.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There should be a van coming\Nto pick us up any minute now.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.98,0:02:50.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, what a great view.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.64,0:02:53.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}? Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.81,0:02:54.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Carsick.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.36,0:02:58.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave it to Hotaro to find something\Nso small to complain about.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.44,0:03:01.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was just an hour and a half.\NWhat a sad sack.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.74,0:03:03.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to say, Mayaka,\NI'm impressed you got us rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.07,0:03:07.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have some relatives who run a tourist\Ninn, but they're renovating it right now,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.87,0:03:10.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and can't take in any customers,\Nso they're letting us stay for free.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.38,0:03:16.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're here, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.42,0:03:18.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, we're here, we're here!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.96,0:03:21.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki! Snap to it,\Nor we'll leave you behind!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.88,0:03:24.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've finally made it to our inn!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.76,0:03:29.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for coming! Welcome to Seizanso!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.77,0:03:29.39,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Seizanso
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.73,0:03:34.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the older sister, Zenna Rie,\Nand her younger sister, Zenna Kayo.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.40,0:03:35.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.44,0:03:37.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're now in 6th grade\Nand 4th grade, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.82,0:03:39.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They've grown even tall...\NHyah!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.40,0:03:40.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sis!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.32,0:03:42.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your rooms are on the\Nsecond floor, at the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.74,0:03:48.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow! Hotaro, hurry, hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.00,0:03:52.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a room with quite\Na nice view, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.92,0:03:55.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't so bad, once in a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.75,0:04:00.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Though, even if it's a lot to ask,\Ncoming alone would have held more charm.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.34,0:04:02.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You, traveling alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.72,0:04:05.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ha! That's a laugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.34,0:04:08.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't forget that it's because\NChitanda-{\i1}san {\i0}planned this trip
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.72,0:04:11.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and Mayaka had the connections\Nthat we're even here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.77,0:04:13.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmph.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.81,0:04:15.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Time to eat!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.02,0:04:16.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're having dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.44,0:04:19.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You heard them. Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.95,0:04:25.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cheese?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.12,0:04:29.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stew... gratin... cheese fondue...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.45,0:04:32.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cold shabu-shabu?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.08,0:04:32.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ready, everyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.96,0:04:34.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for this meal.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.21,0:04:37.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's dessert afterward, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.04,0:04:38.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it cheesecake?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.04,0:04:40.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How did you know?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.05,0:04:41.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I could smell it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.55,0:04:42.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.97,0:04:43.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.84,0:04:45.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just like Maya-{\i1}neechan {\i0}said, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.43,0:04:47.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you tell them, Ibara?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.93,0:04:49.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's all set off fireworks tomorrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.97,0:04:50.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That sounds nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.72,0:04:53.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know! Dad bought some for us yesterday...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.27,0:04:55.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa, what are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.27,0:04:57.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sorry, Sis.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.06,0:04:57.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.52,0:04:59.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.65,0:05:00.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you burn yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.77,0:05:01.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.73,0:05:04.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez, be more careful, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.90,0:05:07.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was filling. Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.20,0:05:11.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Has Satoshi gone to the baths already?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.75,0:05:23.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This {\i1}is {\i0}a hot springs inn\Nthat we've come to, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.13,0:05:24.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.88,0:05:29.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I may ask, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0},\Nwhere are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.68,0:05:31.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Same place as you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.26,0:05:32.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's Ibara?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.35,0:05:34.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The children took her away somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.64,0:05:36.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive me for asking out of the blue,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.85,0:05:40.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}, what is your sister like?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.11,0:05:42.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That really is out of the blue.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.23,0:05:45.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to mention it, Chitanda,\Nyou're an only child, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.78,0:05:46.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My sister, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.45,0:05:48.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's a real character,\Nin more ways than one,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.95,0:05:51.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and she's also brilliant,\Nin more ways than one.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.08,0:05:54.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think I could\Noutshine her in any area.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.12,0:05:54.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.75,0:05:58.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then again, I've never\Nwanted to outshine her.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.46,0:06:03.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what suddenly makes\Nyou ask about my sister?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.50,0:06:06.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seeing the Zenna sisters?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.26,0:06:07.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As a matter of fact,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.88,0:06:11.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've always wanted siblings.\NAn older sister or a younger brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.43,0:06:15.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you think it would be great to have someone\Nnearby with whom you can always feel at home?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.52,0:06:16.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.69,0:06:20.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I suspect that the nice young lady\Nis a bit too good-natured.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.94,0:06:22.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't she dreaming a little too much?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.73,0:06:26.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Siblings aren't actually all that terrific.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.49,0:06:31.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This doesn't appear to have mixed bathing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.28,0:06:33.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course it doesn't!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.29,0:06:38.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.58,0:06:39.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Satoshi's here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.84,0:06:49.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad! Grandpa! Hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.01,0:06:51.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.68,0:06:56.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, this is bigger than I expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.08,0:07:17.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Hotaro! You're here!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.79,0:07:21.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, this hot water is great!\NIt penetrates right through your body!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.62,0:07:24.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It could be dangerous if too much\Nwater mixed in with your blood!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.29,0:07:27.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a silly thing to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.25,0:07:31.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Although, it is nice to have some\Nevidence that you are relaxing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.59,0:07:32.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmph.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.97,0:07:39.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that Chitanda?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.63,0:08:07.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki! What happened?! Is he okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.71,0:08:09.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He got dizzy from the baths.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.46,0:08:10.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.55,0:08:12.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you ever heard of\Nanything so pathetic?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.76,0:08:14.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He wasn't even in there\Nhalf as long as I was,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.09,0:08:17.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but before I knew it, he had fainted.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.18,0:08:19.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I don't believe you...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.23,0:08:29.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ugh... Sorry to put you out, both of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.69,0:08:32.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are quite welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.49,0:08:37.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki, you are simply destined never\Nto be able to enjoy an event, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.83,0:08:40.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Absolutely right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.66,0:08:43.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I had some leftover carsickness, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.83,0:08:44.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I feel sick.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.05,0:08:58.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that Chitanda?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.35,0:09:01.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}, are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.68,0:09:02.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not really.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.06,0:09:06.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're still so hot, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.73,0:09:08.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you want me to wring you out a towel?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.40,0:09:13.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No... I don't want one!\NAh, I'm going to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.40,0:09:18.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry for casting a damper\Non such a nice outing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.20,0:09:19.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.83,0:09:24.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The rest of us are talking about\Ntelling ghost stories now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.08,0:09:28.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you start feeling any better,\Nplease come and join us, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.33,0:09:30.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, take care.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.13,0:09:30.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.85,0:09:42.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's still not even 8:00?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.39,0:09:48.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Taiko {\i0}drums?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.15,0:09:52.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, we could have gotten by\Nwithout having to build another hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.98,0:09:56.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is the next room open, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.90,0:09:58.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.32,0:09:59.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A secret?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.57,0:10:02.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Long ago, there was this brooding\Nold guest who stayed here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.16,0:10:05.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was put in Room 7 of the main hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.66,0:10:09.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He said he didn't want to\Neat, and he didn't need a futon,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.66,0:10:10.92,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,7
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.21,0:10:10.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and to just stay away from him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.29,0:10:15.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But he paid in advance,\Nand he came at a busy time,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.05,0:10:17.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so they said that he was a perfect fit.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.13,0:10:20.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, that evening,\Nthere was a terrible scream!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.30,0:10:21.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A scream?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.01,0:10:26.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There in Room 7 was the shadowy figure of a person,\Ndimly visible with a rope around his neck,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.18,0:10:28.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,slowly swaying back and forth,\Nthe story goes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.19,0:10:32.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Word was that this man had taken money\Nfrom the company he worked for.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.65,0:10:34.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I was waiting for!\NCut that out!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.82,0:10:38.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since that happened,\Nguests that have stayed in Room 7
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.70,0:10:39.36,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,2
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.70,0:10:41.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,say that there's something in the room...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.36,0:10:39.95,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,3
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.95,0:10:40.57,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,4
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.57,0:10:41.24,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,5
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.24,0:10:41.78,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,6
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.24,0:10:43.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that there are shadows\Nthat appear during the night.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.78,0:10:42.41,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,7
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.41,0:10:43.24,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,8
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.83,0:10:47.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, the ninth guest that stayed there...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.83,0:10:49.46,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,9
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.83,0:10:49.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened to them?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.46,0:10:53.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sometime during the night,\Nthey suddenly got sick and died!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.00,0:10:53.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.71,0:10:54.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's more like it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.96,0:10:55.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I said knock it off!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.63,0:10:59.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, Grandma called in an exorcist,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.05,0:11:01.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and then also had this second hall built
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.68,0:11:04.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to keep any bad rumors from spreading.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.89,0:11:06.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where is this Room 7?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.47,0:11:10.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, it's the room you can see\Nthrough the window, straight ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.02,0:11:13.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We live down on the first floor,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.06,0:11:15.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and make sure not to go to\Nthe second floor very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.44,0:11:17.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You're kidding, right? It's a joke!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.86,0:11:20.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, you can't tell anyone this story!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.57,0:11:22.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How quaint. Truly. Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.00,0:11:34.00,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Risshu {\i0}('Dawn of Autumn')\NThe time of the first stirrings of autumn
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.25,0:11:34.00,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Hyouka
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.22,0:11:44.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's morning, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.51,0:11:46.76,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,The Fuji Room
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.02,0:11:49.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.27,0:11:51.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning. Where are Chitanda and Ibara?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.02,0:11:53.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.56,0:11:55.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.44,0:11:57.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Last night, after midnight,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.98,0:12:01.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a warm breeze woke me up,\Nand when I rolled over,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.45,0:12:05.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw the silhouette of a hanging man\Nin the room across the way,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.28,0:12:06.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,slowly swinging back and forth!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.74,0:12:09.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's pretty rare to see Ibara so shaken up.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.58,0:12:12.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tough luck for Satoshi,\Nmissing a sight like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.79,0:12:13.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for breakfast.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.87,0:12:15.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How were the open-air baths?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.54,0:12:17.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They were extremely refreshing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.34,0:12:18.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Terrific!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.21,0:12:19.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.21,0:12:19.46,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Rie
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.46,0:12:21.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I hope your futon was nice and fluffy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.76,0:12:24.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I slept quite well.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.22,0:12:27.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't look like there's one for Kayo.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.35,0:12:31.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't realize that you couldn't handle\Na story like that, Maya-{\i1}neechan{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.02,0:12:35.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm {\i1}not {\i0}afraid of ghosts. But when\NI saw what I did point-blank...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.73,0:12:37.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a limit to how\Ncreeped-out I can stand being!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.86,0:12:40.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maya-{\i1}neechan{\i0}, you saw it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.57,0:12:42.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw it! I totally saw it!\NI really saw it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.11,0:12:46.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sis, you told them the story?\NDad said never to tell anyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.87,0:12:50.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, buzz off. Who cares?\NIt's Maya-{\i1}neechan{\i0}, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.67,0:12:55.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.92,0:12:57.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.25,0:13:01.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,what do you think about\Nwhat Mayaka-{\i1}san {\i0}says?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.26,0:13:04.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,About seeing the silhouette\Nof a hanging man?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.05,0:13:08.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you can't dismiss that it's an old staple,\Nsomething obligatory, and that's why it lives on.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.26,0:13:12.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So then, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}, do you think that\Nwhat Mayaka-{\i1}san {\i0}says is true?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.18,0:13:13.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.10,0:13:17.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then maybe I was mistaken.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.40,0:13:19.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm? What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.36,0:13:25.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw it, too... the silhouette\Nof a hanging man.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.16,0:13:29.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayaka-{\i1}san {\i0}had woken up,\Nso I woke up, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.58,0:13:31.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I did, I saw it\Nsuspended in the darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.83,0:13:32.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ho...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.58,0:13:34.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought that my mind could\Nbe playing tricks on me,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.83,0:13:37.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but Mayaka-{\i1}san {\i0}saw the\Nsame thing, too, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.54,0:13:41.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You must have mistook what you saw.\NLike in that saying yesterday...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.09,0:13:42.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Upon seeing the ghost's true nature..."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.76,0:13:44.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a beckoning flower? Hm...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.72,0:13:49.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If that's true, then what\Ndid we see that fooled us?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.05,0:13:51.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.85,0:13:54.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're right, then tell us\Nwhat we {\i1}did {\i0}see that fooled us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.22,0:13:55.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do I have to...\NOreki-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.19,0:13:59.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's investigate this together!\NI am so curious!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.65,0:14:02.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, Chi-{\i1}chan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.86,0:14:05.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I promised Rie that I would look over\Nher summer vacation homework.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.03,0:14:09.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave it to us! We will be sure to\Nfind out the truth behind this!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.82,0:14:11.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.16,0:14:12.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's asking {\i1}me {\i0}"right"?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.91,0:14:17.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, what has to be done is at\Nleast close by. Pardon the intrusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.58,0:14:21.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So then, you saw this shadow\Ndirectly across from your room?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.79,0:14:23.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.30,0:14:24.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How big?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.21,0:14:26.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't too big, and it\Nwasn't too little, I'd say.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.97,0:14:28.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shape?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.05,0:14:29.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't exactly remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.89,0:14:30.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Color?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.59,0:14:32.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know. It was in shadow.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.60,0:14:34.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shadow, huh? So you're saying\Nthat it was lit from behind,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.93,0:14:37.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so it looked like the\Nsilhouette of a person.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.48,0:14:39.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I believe so, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.06,0:14:40.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Backlit, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.65,0:14:43.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only source of light at night\Nwould have been the moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.57,0:14:49.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think so, too. The moon was pretty\Nbright last night. Would that mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.66,0:14:50.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.45,0:14:53.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chitanda, what time did you finish\Nyour ghost stories and go to sleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.53,0:14:54.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see, it was 10:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.99,0:14:56.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the shutters at that time?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.25,0:14:58.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I believe they were closed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.29,0:14:58.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.46,0:15:03.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As long as those shutters were closed,\Nthere could be no shadow.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.00,0:15:04.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now we're running into a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.50,0:15:08.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At this point, we'll need to\Ncheck out Room 7 in the main hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.30,0:15:12.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is nice and mysterious! I really\Nam glad we went on this outing!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.80,0:15:14.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd have been glad if we hadn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.43,0:15:15.43,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,No Admittance
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.52,0:15:19.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.18,0:15:21.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes, what is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.69,0:15:22.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.65,0:15:24.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?\NI suck with kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.36,0:15:25.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.82,0:15:27.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kayo-{\i1}san{\i0}, can we have a moment?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.45,0:15:33.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'd like to go into the main hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.37,0:15:35.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The main hall? But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.99,0:15:39.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We are investigating the\Nhanging-man shadow.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.25,0:15:41.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'd like you to show us Room 7.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.58,0:15:44.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, I can't right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.75,0:15:48.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My sister would get mad at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.51,0:15:50.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, at least tell us one thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.51,0:15:52.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that room still a guest room?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.72,0:15:58.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. Only the baths and the dining room\Nin the main hall are used by guests.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.02,0:16:00.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, the room is vacant?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.64,0:16:03.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The whole second floor\Nis used for storage now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.56,0:16:05.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,May I go now?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.23,0:16:09.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you. You've been very helpful...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.44,0:16:11.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She hates me, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.20,0:16:15.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't matter, does it?\NShe's probably just scared of big men.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.07,0:16:16.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's so cute!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.37,0:16:20.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will not being able to see\NRoom 7 pose a problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.83,0:16:25.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not so much a problem as a hassle.\NWe can't inspect the scene, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.75,0:16:28.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my! I remember having these!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.34,0:16:28.59,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Rie
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.55,0:16:30.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.13,0:16:32.26,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Rie
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.80,0:16:35.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Morning radio calisthenics.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.59,0:16:38.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I went to these, up until\Nthe year before last.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.76,0:16:42.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Until her second year of\Nmiddle school? Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.19,0:16:45.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's check around the\Nother side, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.23,0:16:49.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did it rain last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.61,0:16:51.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, a small shower.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.82,0:16:54.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In order for there to be a shadow seen,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.66,0:16:58.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,both the east and west side shutters\Nwould have to have been open.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.08,0:17:01.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.41,0:17:04.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lunch is ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.17,0:17:07.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for lunch!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.30,0:17:15.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It sure must be nice,\Nhaving a sister, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.38,0:17:18.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah? Chitanda-{\i1}san{\i0},\Ndo you wish you had a sister?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.43,0:17:19.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.51,0:17:21.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, did you find out anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.39,0:17:22.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.02,0:17:25.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're still just getting started.\NI have a theory, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.64,0:17:26.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah? Let's hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.31,0:17:29.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Hm...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.19,0:17:30.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, see here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.52,0:17:34.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What exactly are you talking about?\NDon't go shutting me out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.19,0:17:38.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody's shutting you out. Where is it you're\Nalways disappearing to? We never see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.91,0:17:40.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't get it, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.70,0:17:43.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's good manners to go and visit\Nthe hot springs again and again.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.08,0:17:44.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, is that a fact?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.46,0:17:47.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ta-da! How do you like my yukata?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.21,0:17:48.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, that's so neat!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.96,0:17:49.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that nice?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.75,0:17:53.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I finally had one bought for me\Nat the start of summer vacation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.51,0:17:55.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've said you wanted one\Nfor a long time, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.01,0:17:56.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm-hm!\NNice taste, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.51,0:17:58.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong with it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.09,0:17:59.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That sash.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.64,0:18:01.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll bet it's an imitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.10,0:18:02.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean, it's a mutant?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.85,0:18:06.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not "mutation," {\i1}imitation{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.02,0:18:09.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The bow is a separate piece,\Nclipped onto the sash.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.19,0:18:11.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't acknowledge that\Nas being a yukata.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.19,0:18:13.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.07,0:18:18.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is something the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.45,0:18:24.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if I might have fallen under\Nthe hanged shadow's curse, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.33,0:18:31.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go to the same hot\Nspring as yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.59,0:18:33.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.21,0:18:36.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The hanged shadow...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.26,0:18:40.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a product of Ibara and\NChitanda's false impression.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.30,0:18:41.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A beckoning flower.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.30,0:18:45.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But still, there's one piece missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.52,0:18:50.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go back together, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.77,0:18:53.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Satoshi's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.61,0:18:59.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You were just there sitting next to\Nus while eating, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.95,0:19:01.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When did you manage to get here?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.66,0:19:04.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, if you slide down the\Ncliff behind Seizanso,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.83,0:19:06.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it leads right behind here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.54,0:19:11.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sliding down a cliff, just to take a\Nshortcut? That's just like Satoshi.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.05,0:19:19.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have an explanation\Nthat will satisfy Chitanda.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.88,0:19:22.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The source of the shadow isn't too hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.14,0:19:25.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The question is, how did\Nit come to be there?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.56,0:19:28.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hotaro, don't tell me you're dizzy again.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.02,0:19:32.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, was there some kind of\Nbig event last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.40,0:19:33.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, Hotaro, you fainted.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.69,0:19:35.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, not me!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.19,0:19:37.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, we all told ghost stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.82,0:19:39.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was surrounded by more\Ngirls than I could handle.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.61,0:19:41.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, something more official.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.99,0:19:44.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you mention it,\Nthere was a summer festival.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.37,0:19:46.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You heard the {\i1}taiko {\i0}drums, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.45,0:19:47.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Taiko {\i0}drums...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.37,0:19:53.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it! A summer festival!\NThat explains it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.04,0:19:55.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So? Does that mean something?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.51,0:20:05.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So about the hanged shadow...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.76,0:20:07.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was probably a yukata,\Nhanging on a hanger.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.39,0:20:08.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.98,0:20:14.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would there be a yukata hanging there?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.27,0:20:17.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's more, it's strange that\Nboth shutters would be open,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.19,0:20:18.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to show us the yukata's shadow.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.15,0:20:21.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't done to show you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.53,0:20:22.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then...?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.61,0:20:24.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was hung up to dry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.49,0:20:25.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The yukata was wet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.41,0:20:28.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The reason the shutters were open
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.12,0:20:30.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was to let the breeze through,\Nto dry it quicker.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.95,0:20:31.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.58,0:20:33.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because it rained.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.67,0:20:36.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not that. Why was it in Room 7?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.71,0:20:40.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To prevent anyone from seeing\Nit being hung up to dry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.51,0:20:42.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But {\i1}we {\i0}saw it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.01,0:20:42.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.13,0:20:45.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They were trying to hide\Nit from the family.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.64,0:20:46.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.43,0:20:50.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The one who hung up the yukata was Kayo.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.27,0:20:55.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kayo was envious of Rie's yukata,\Nand wanted to wear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.19,0:20:57.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I doubt Rie would lend it to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.15,0:20:59.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why not? They're sisters.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.36,0:21:04.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you notice? Rie is the kind of\Ngirl who clearly marks which cup,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.61,0:21:08.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,which radio calisthenics card,\Nand which ball are hers.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.08,0:21:11.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She couldn't ask Rie to lend her\Nher yukata if she's like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.24,0:21:11.83,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Rie
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.83,0:21:13.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.75,0:21:17.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Kayo still wanted to wear it.\NSo she snuck it out,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.38,0:21:22.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and wore it to the summer festival\Nyesterday. That was at 8:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.30,0:21:24.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kayo-{\i1}san {\i0}went to the summer festival?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.01,0:21:28.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw someone leaving the house\Nat 8:00 last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.60,0:21:33.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kayo wasn't there when you were\Ntelling ghost stories, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.77,0:21:36.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right; Kayo-{\i1}san {\i0}was not there.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.10,0:21:40.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But then, Kayo ran into some bad luck\Nwhile she was enjoying the festival.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.52,0:21:42.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It started raining.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.07,0:21:46.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The rain let up quickly,\Nbut the yukata was wet.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.20,0:21:48.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kayo remembered we would be\Nsetting off fireworks the next day.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.37,0:21:53.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rie would undoubtedly want\Nto wear the yukata for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.45,0:21:56.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If the yukata wasn't dry by tomorrow,\NRie would blame her for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.08,0:22:00.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The family would see it on\Nthe main hall's first floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.34,0:22:01.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The other hall was out of the question.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.84,0:22:04.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She can't use the dryer\Nin the middle of the night.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.05,0:22:07.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why Kayo waited until\Neveryone was asleep,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.63,0:22:11.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and dried the yukata in the most distant\Nroom on the main hall's second floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.31,0:22:14.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Kayo's run of bad luck would continue.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.14,0:22:20.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Moonlight shone in through the open window,\Nrevealing the hanged shadow.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.06,0:22:21.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then the last bit of bad luck came
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.07,0:22:24.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when we started investigating\Nthe hanging shadow.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.32,0:22:27.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kayo had to have been agonizing.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.86,0:22:31.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No doubt that was Kayo's shadow\NI saw between the sliding doors.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.54,0:22:34.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kayo-{\i1}san{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.45,0:22:38.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She put the yukata back\Nearly in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.21,0:22:41.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unlike Rie, Kayo went to radio\Ncalisthenics every morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.75,0:22:44.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It would have been easy to return it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.46,0:22:47.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.05,0:22:49.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not going tell Ibara about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.76,0:22:52.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure there could be some\Nfamily issues at work here.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.43,0:22:55.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If that's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.43,0:23:00.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it would mean that the two\Nof them don't get along.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.44,0:23:06.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, a sister who won't\Nlend you her yukata...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.70,0:23:16.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that what siblings do?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.08,0:23:16.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.50,0:23:21.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,wanted a sibling. An older\Nsister I could respect,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.67,0:23:23.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or an adorable younger brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.09,0:23:31.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if the sibling\Nthat Chitanda desired
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.76,0:23:33.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was a "beckoning flower."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.89,0:23:38.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's so hot...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.35,0:23:43.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.15,0:23:44.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm-hm.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.74,0:24:00.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, maybe they're not all\N"beckoning flowers," either.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.96,0:24:07.92,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Tonight it turns to love{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.92,0:24:11.68,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Meet me in a pleasant dream{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.68,0:24:15.68,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Make sure that you find me, okay?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.68,0:24:20.98,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Our snooze-time date{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.16,0:24:41.21,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The heat of your budding warmth troubles me{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.00,0:24:52.01,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Don't you understand how I feel yet?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.43,0:24:58.93,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There isn't supposed to be\Nany significance in your glance{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.93,0:25:04.27,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I mean, it's the same one\Nyou give all your friends{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.27,0:25:10.03,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The tiny wishing star fading\Ninto the morning light{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.03,0:25:14.99,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and the magic it works during the night\N(I wish you would notice){\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.99,0:25:18.08,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Tonight it turns to love{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.08,0:25:21.79,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Meet me in a pleasant dream{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.79,0:25:25.79,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Make sure that you find me, okay?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.79,0:25:31.05,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Our snooze-time date{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.76,0:25:43.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, "Let's Go To the Screening!"
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.47,0:25:43.45,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's Go To the Screening!
